Brazilian Stock Movers: BM&FBovespa, Petrobras, Ultrapar, Vale

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-08-18T20:19:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/brazilian-stock-movers-bm-fbovespa-petrobras-ultrapar-vale.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index tumbled 3.5 percent to 53,134.10.  BM&FBovespa SA (BVMF3)  (BVMF3 BS) declined 3.9 percent to 8.89
reais. The operator of  Latin America ’s biggest securities
exchange was cut to “neutral” from “buy” at Bank of America
Corp., which cited measures taken by the Brazilian government to
curb currency gains.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  (PETR4 BS) slumped 2.7 percent to
20.30 reais while  Vale SA (VALE3)  (VALE5 BS) sank 5 percent to 38.30
reais.  Brazil ’s state-controlled oil company and the world’s
largest iron-ore producer followed crude and metals prices
lower.  Ultrapar Participacoes SA (UGPA3 BS) fell 1.4 percent to
26.85 reais. The Brazilian fuels and petrochemicals group was
cut to “underweight” from “equal-weight” at Morgan Stanley.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in  Sao Paulo  at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
